article.headline: McMaryion, Rivers help Fresno State beat Nevada 21-3
article.description: Marcus McMaryion was 20-of-28 passing for 241 yards and Ronnie Rivers scored two touchdowns to help Fresno State beat Nevada 21-3 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: McMaryion, Rivers help Fresno State beat Nevada 21-3

images.name: Fresno State takes lead with 19-yard TD
images.caption: Marcus McMaryion connects with Ronnie Rivers who runs in for a 19-yard touchdown.

video.headline: Fresno State takes lead with 19-yard TD
video.caption: Marcus McMaryion connects with Ronnie Rivers who runs in for a 19-yard touchdown.
video.title: Fresno State takes lead with 19-yard TD
video.description: Marcus McMaryion connects with Ronnie Rivers who runs in for a 19-yard touchdown.

article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Marcus McMaryion was 20-of-28 passing for 241 yards and Ronnie Rivers scored two touchdowns to help Fresno State beat Nevada 21-3 on Saturday night. McMaryion threw touchdowns passes to Rivers and KeeSean Johnson, who finished with seven receptions for 65 yards. Fresno State (4-1, 1-0 Mountain West), which came in averaging 45 points and 439.8 total yards per game, was limited to a season-low 271 yards but forced three Nevada turnovers. Rivers took a screen pass 19 yards for a score with 13:11 left in the second quarter and, after Nevada's Ramiz Ahmed made a 41-yard field goal, the Bulldogs took a 7-3 lead into halftime. Rivers, on fourth down, scored on a 2-yard run early in the third quarter and Johnson's 27-yard TD reception capped the scoring midway through the fourth. Cristian Solano was 22-of-43 passing for 195 yards with three interceptions and added 23 carries for 71 yards for Nevada (3-3, 1-1). Kaleb Fossum had 12 receptions for 97 yards.
